lines.transliteration:
Para Rhoustikou to labein phantasian tou chrēizein diorthōseōs kai therapeias tou ēthous; kai to mē ektrapēnai eis zēlon sophistikon, mēde to sungraphein peri tōn theōrēmatōn, ē protreptika logaria dialegesthai, ē phantasioplēktōs ton askētikon ē ton energētikon andra epideiknusthai;
kai to apostēnai rhētorikēs kai poiētikēs kai asteiologias; kai to mē en stolēi kat' oikon peripatein mēde ta toiauta poiein; kai to ta epistolia aphelōs graphein, oion to hup autou toutou apo Sinoessēs tēi mētri mou graphen;
kai to pros tous chalepēnantas kai plēmmelēsantas euanaklētōs kai eudiallaktōs, epeidan tachista autoi epanelthein ethelēsōsi, diakeisthai; kai to akribōs anaginōskein kai mē arkeisthai perinoounta holoscherōs mēde tois perilalousi tacheōs sunkatatithesthai; kai to entuchein tois Epiktēteiois hupomnēmasin, hōn oikothen metedōken.

Para Sextou to eumenes; kai to paradeigma tou oikou tou patronomoumenou; kai tēn ennoian tou kata phusin zēn; kai to semnon aplastōs; kai to stochastikon tōn philōn kēdemonikōs; kai to anektikon tōn idiōtōn kai to atheōrēton oiomenōn;
kai to pros pantas euarmoston, hōste kolakeias men pasēs prosēnesteran einai tēn homilian autou, aidesimōtaton de autois ekeinois par' auton ekeinon ton kairon einai; kai to katalēptikōs kai hodōi exeuretikon te kai taktikon tōn eis bion anankaiōn dogmatōn;
kai to mēde emphasin pote orgēs ē allou tinos pathous paraschein, alla hama men apathestaton einai, hama de philostorgotaton; kai to euphēmon apsophēti kai to polumathes anepiphantōs.

Para Maximou to kratein heautou kai kata mēden periphoron einai; kai to euthumon en te tais allais peristasesi kai en tais nosois; kai to eukraton tou ēthous kai meilichion kai geraron; kai to ou schetliōs katergastikon tōn prokeimenōn;
kai to pantas autōi pisteuein peri hōn legoi hoti outōs phronei, kai peri hōn prattoi hoti ou kakōs prattei. kai to athaumaston kai anekplēkton kai mēdamou epeigomenon ē oknoun ē amēchanoun ē katēphes ē prossesēros, ē palin thumoumenon ē huphorōmenon;
kai to euergetikon kai to sungnōmonikon kai to apseudes; kai to adiastrophou mallon ē diorthoumenou phantasian parechein; kai hoti oute ōiēthē an pote tis huperorasthai hup' autou oute hupemeinen an kreittona autou auton hupolabein; kai to eucharientizesthai.

Para tou patros to hēmeron kai menetikon asaleutōs epi tōn exētasmenōs krithentōn; kai to akenodoxon peri tas dokousas timas; kai to philoponon kai endeleches; kai to akoustikon tōn echontōn ti koinōpheles eispherein; kai to aparatreptōs tou kat' axian aponemētikon hekastōi; kai to empeiron pou men chreia entaseōs, pou de aneseōs;
kai to pausai ta peri tous erōtas tōn; meirakiōn; kai hē koinonoēmosunē kai to epheisthai tois philois mēte sundeipnein autōi pantōs mēte sunapodēmein epanankes, aei de homoion auton katalambanesthai hupo tōn dia chreias tinas apoleiphthentōn; kai to zētētikon akribōs en tois sumbouliois kai epimonon, all' ou to proapestē tēs ereunēs, arkestheis tais procheirois phantasiais; kai to diatērētikon tōn philōn kai mēdamou hapsikoron mēde epimanes; kai to autarkes en panti kai to phaidron;
kai to porrōthen pronoētikon kai tōn elachistōn prodioikētikon atragōidōs; kai to tas epiboēseis kai pasan kolakeian ep' autou sustalēnan kai to phulaktikon aei tōn anankaiōn tēi archēi kai tamieutikon tēs chorēgias kai hupomenetikon tēs epi tōn toioutōn tinōn kataitiaseōs; kai to mēte peri theous deisidaimon mēte peri anthrōpous dēmokopikon ē areskeutikon ē ochlochares, alla nēphon en pasi kai bebaion kai mēdamou apeirokalon mēde kainotomon;
kai to tois eis eumareian biou pherousi ti, hōn hē tuchē pareiche dapsileian, chrēstikon atuphōs hama kai aprophasistōs, hōste parontōn men anepitēdeutōs haptesthai, apontōn de mē deisthai; kai to mēde an tina eipein mēte hoti sophistēs mēte hoti ouernaklos mēte hoti scholastikos, all' hoti anēr pepeiros, teleios, akolakeutos, proestanai dunamenos kai tōn heautou kai allōn.
pros toutois de kai to timētikon tōn alēthōs philosophountōn, tois de allois ouk exoneidistikon oude mēn euparagōgon hup' autōn; eti de to euomilon kai euchari ou katakorōs; kai to tou idiou sōmatos epimelētikon emmetrōs, oute hōs an tis philozōos oute pros kallōpismon oute mēn oligōrōs, all' hōste dia tēn idian prosochēn eis oligista iatrikēs chrēizein ē pharmakōn kai epithematōn ektos;
malista de to parachōrētikon abaskanōs tois dunamin tina kektēmenois, oion tēn phrastikēn ē tēn ex historias nomōn ē ethōn ē allōn tinōn pragmatōn, kai suspoudastikon autois, hina hekastoi kata ta idia proterēmata eudokimōsi; panta de kata ta patria prassōn, oude auto touto epitēdeuōn phainesthai, to ta patria phulassein.
eti de to mē eumetakinēton kai rhiptastikon, alla kai topois kai pragmasi tois autois endiatriptikon; kai to meta tous paroxusmous tēs kephalalgias nearon euthus kai akmaion pros ta sunēthē erga; kai to mē einai autōi polla ta aporrēta, all' oligista kai spaniōtata kai tauta huper tōn koinōn monōn; kai to emphron kai memetrēmenon en te theōriōn epitelesei kai ergōn kataskeuais kai dianomais kai tois toioutois, ho estin anthrōpou pros auto to deon prachthēnai dedorkotos, ou pros tēn epi tois prachtheisin eudoxian.
ouk aōri loustēs, ouchi philoikodomos, ou peri tas edōdas epinoētēs, ou peri esthētōn huphas kai chroas, ou peri sōmatōn hōras. hē apo Lōriou stolē anagousa apo tēs katō epauleōs; chitōn en Lanoubiōi ta polla; tōi phelōnēi en Tousklois paraitoumenōi hōs echrēsato kai pas ho toioutos tropos.
ouden apēnes oude mēn adusōpēton oude labron oude hōst' an tina eipein pote; heōs hidrōtos; alla panta dieilēmmena lelogisthai hōs epi scholēs, atarachōs, tetagmenōs, errōmenōs, sumphōnōs heautois. epharmoseie d' an autōi to peri tou Sōkratous mnēmoneuomenon, hoti kai apechesthai kai apolauein edunato toutōn, hōn oi polloi pros te tas apochas asthenōs kai pros tas apolauseis endotikōs echousi.
to de ischuein kai enkarterein kai ennēphein hekaterōi andros estin artion kai aēttēton psuchēn echontos, oion en tēi nosōi tēi Maximou.
